tags.name: St Vincent De Paul Day Care
New Bantama M/A KO and Primary Schools
Kumasi Wesley Girls' Senior High School
Old Tafo Methodist Prim A,B, & JHS

tags.description: Angel Senior High School, established in 2006, is situated at Kronum-Abouhia, about four hundred meters away from Central Kumasi-Offinso main road.
tags.name: Angel Educational Complex Senior High School

tags.description: Kwasi Oppong Senior High school, established in 2009, is a private institution founded by Elder Dr. Kwasi Oppong, a Christian businessman with a view of inculcating positive virtues in today’s young generation.
tags.name: Kwasi Oppong Senior High School

tags.description: The School was established in 2004 as a purely girls’ school and is located on the former premises of the Osei Kyeretwie Senior High School at Dichemso.
tags.name: Serwaa Nyarko Girls' Senior High School
tags.wikipedia: en:Serwaa Nyarko Girls' Senior High School

tags.description: The School was established in 1949 by the Late Otumfo Sir Osei Agyemang Prempeh II, the then Asantehene in collaboration with the Presbyterian and Methodist Churches, and under the first Headmaster Rev. S. N. Pearson.
tags.name: Prempeh College

tags.description: The school was founded in 1973 by Anglican missionaries. It is situated at Asem, a suburb of Kumasi in the Ashanti Region of Ghana. It is popularly known by the acronym KASS. Both present and past students are known as DISCIPLES
tags.name: Kumasi Anglican Senior High School

tags.description: Kumasi Girls was started as a Private Secondary School for girls in 1953 by Mr Caxton Williams, a Sierra Leonean. At first the school was situated at Susanso, near Bomso Junction, on the Kumasi-Accra road.
tags.name: Kumasi Girls' Senior High School

tags.description: The school was established in 1951 by Ghana’s first president Dr. Kwame Nkrumah. The school however started in 1960 with funds from the Ghana Education Trust
tags.name: Yaa Asantewaa Girls' Senior High School

tags.description: Armed Forces Senior High Technical School is located within the Old Uaddara Barracks, the former home of the 4 Battalion of Infantry (4BN), near Okomfo Anokye Teaching Hospital in Kumasi.
tags.name: Armed Forces Senior High/Technical School

tags.description: An association called Asante Youth Association (AYA) at its meeting at K.O Methodist School in 1952 mooted the idea of establishing a Secondary School in the locality to reduce cost factors involved in seeking secondary education down south.
tags.name: Asanteman Senior High School

tags.description: The School started as a private secondary school in 1969, and was absorbed into the public schools stream in the 2009/2010 academic year. The school is a mission school, therefore very religious.
tags.name: Islamic Senior High School

tags.description: The school is the first second cycle institution in Ashanti Religion and it was established in 1937 by the late J.T. Roberts, a Sierra Leonne man, in September 1962, and was absorbed into the Public System by the Ministry of Education.
tags.name: Osei Kyeretwie Senior High School
Progressive Shalom Int. School - New Site

tags.description: The school, until recently (2008), known as Kumasi Secondary Technical school, was established as a coeducational institution in 1991.
tags.name: Kumasi Senior High/Technical School

tags.description: Opoku Ware School, originally called the Yaa Asantewaa College, was established by the Gold Coast Government at the request of the Catholic Church in Ashanti Region to cater for boys’ education, as an alternative to travelling to St. Augustine’s College
tags.name: Opoku Ware School

tags.description: The school was established by the government of Ghana in October 1975 as a community school named Trabuom Secondary School. The school was adopted by Otumfuo Osei Tutu II named it after his mother.
tags.name: Afua Kobi Ampem Girls' Senior High School

tags.description: The School is located at Nzema, inside Kwadaso Agric College Campus and was established in November 2016, as a Day School, to make education accessible to the rural community.
tags.name: Agric Nzema Senior High Scool

tags.description: The School, an initiative of Sheikh Mohammed Kamil Mohammed, started as a private institution in 2003 with 18 students. During the 2011/2012 academic year, the school became a Public or Government Assisted Senior High School.
tags.name: Al-Azariya Islamic Senior High School

tags.description: Denyaseman Catholic Senior High School [DECASHS] was established in 1992, absorbed into the government mainstream in April, 2010, and registered under the Education Act 778 of 2008 as a day/boarding Second Cycle Institution
tags.name: Denyaseman Catholic Senior High School

tags.description: A Government Assisted 2nd cycle institution located at Esaase in the Amansie West District in Ashanti Region. It was established as a community school in 1991 to offer senior high education to children within the Bontefufuom enclave and beyond.
tags.name: Esaase Bontefufuo Senior High/Technical School

tags.description: The school is sited in Manso Adubia on a 50-acre land with a well-arranged compound, made up of green landscape with ornamental plants which provide serene and beautiful environment in the Amansie South District.
tags.name: Manso-Adubia Senior High School

tags.description: Mansoman Senior High School was established on 12th October, 1973. The school is located at Manso Atwere in Amansie West District of Ashanti Region.
tags.name: Mansoman Senior High School

tags.description: Methodist Technical Institute (MTI), Kwadaso was established in 1992 through the initiative of Mr. Sampson Fobi, the Bethel Methodist Church, Kwadaso and the Lutheran Church of Germany and was adopted by the Government of Ghana in 2010
tags.name: Methodist Technical Institute

tags.description: Mpasiatia Senior High Technical School, established on 28th January, 1991, is a mixed school located at Mpasatia, off Abuakwa-Bibiani highway; after Atwima Wioso in the Ashanti Region.
tags.name: Mpasatia Senior High/Technical School

tags.description: Ofoase Kokoben Senior High School is located on the Kumasi-Obuasi Highway, before Anwiankwanta and was established in 2010 by the community and was absorbed into the Public System in 2013
tags.name: Ofoase Kokoben Senior High School

tags.description: Osei Tutu Senior High School is a boys’ school established in 1940 by the Methodist Church. It was named after Otumfuo Osei Tutu I, the founder of the Asante Kingdom.
tags.name: Osei Tutu Senior High School

tags.description: The school, a mission school owned by the Pentecost Church, was established in 2006 and was absorbed by the Government in the 2017/2018 academic year.
tags.name: Pentecost Senior High School

tags.description: The school was established in 1970 by the Catholic Church and is located at Santasi very close to Opoku Ware School. The school was absorbed into the Public System in 2005.
tags.name: St. Hubert Seminary/Senior High School

tags.description: T. I. Ahmadiyya Senior High was established in 1950 and is located in the Kumasi Metropolitan District
tags.name: T. I. Ahmadiyya Senior High School, Kumasi

tags.description: Tawheed Senior High School was established in 2001 and is located in the Asokore-Mampong near the central mosque at Akwatia-Line in Kumasi.
tags.name: Tawheed Senior High School

tags.description: The school was established in 1971 in Toase township. It is located along theAbuakwa-Bibiani main road and 100m away from Nkawie Government Hospital.
tags.name: Toase Senior High School

tags.description: The school was established in 2005 as a Private School to provide secular and Islamic education to Ghanaian youth. It is located at Tafo Nhyiaeso near Moro market, and opposite Glory Oil fuel station.
tags.name: Uthmaniya Senior High School

tags.description: The School was established as a fully Private Nondenominational, Co-educational Institution
tags.name: SEA Senior High School

tags.description: Established in 1991 as a community Senior High with 50 students and 8 teachers, the school has the Latin expression, CARPE DEIM as its motto. This can be loosely translated as, “Make hay whiles the sun shines”
tags.name: Nkawie Senior High/Technical School

tags.description: The School is located at Adobewora and was established in 2016, as a Day School, to make education accessible to the rural community.
tags.name: Adobewora Community Senior High School

tags.description: Prince of Peace Girls Senior High was founded by the then Metropolitan Arch Bishop of the Catholic Church of Kumasi, Most Rev. Dr. Peter Kwasi Sarpong, in October 1982 with Rev. Sr. Erlinda Macatol as the first Headmistress.
tags.name: Prince of Peace Girls' Senior High School
